WEBVTT

00:00.360 --> 00:04.945
[ Birds chirping,
soft music playing ]

00:05.045 --> 00:06.826
[ Loud banging ]

00:06.926 --> 00:08.788
[ Gasps ]

00:08.888 --> 00:12.152
Freya. Freya!
The house is under attack!

00:12.252 --> 00:13.793
Assume battle positions!

00:13.893 --> 00:15.835
Sid, it's okay.
It's just me.

00:15.935 --> 00:17.837
Oh. Whoa.
Uh, what are you doing?

00:17.937 --> 00:19.359
Putting up decorations.

00:19.459 --> 00:20.961
What do you think?

00:21.061 --> 00:22.282
Uh...

00:22.382 --> 00:24.284
I mean, wow.
Cool, right?

00:24.384 --> 00:25.445
It's the heads
of my enemies.

00:25.545 --> 00:26.726
Yeah. No, I see that.

00:26.826 --> 00:28.768
I guess...
I'm just worried

00:28.868 --> 00:33.333
it might come across
as a bit spine-tingling.

00:33.433 --> 00:34.734
How do you mean?
I'm just worried

00:34.834 --> 00:36.336
that our new neighbours
aren't accustomed

00:36.436 --> 00:38.058
to the casual horrors
of the wasteland

00:38.158 --> 00:39.459
in the same way that we are.

00:39.559 --> 00:40.820
Gosh, Sid, I love you,
but I think you're

00:40.920 --> 00:42.102
way off base here.

00:42.202 --> 00:43.263
You really need to
see it plugged in

00:43.363 --> 00:44.344
to get the full effect.

00:44.444 --> 00:45.945
[ Generator whirring ]

00:46.045 --> 00:50.330
[ Heads groaning to "When
the Saints Go Marching In" ]

00:54.574 --> 00:55.835
Yeah, you're right.
It is better like that.

00:55.935 --> 00:57.517
Right?

00:57.617 --> 01:02.162
[ Heads continue groaning ]

01:02.262 --> 01:12.132
♪♪

01:12.232 --> 01:15.455
Your subjects in Old New Jersey
can't pay your tribute on time

01:15.555 --> 01:17.777
on account of
an extended Nuclear Winter.

01:17.877 --> 01:20.380
It's too bad for them.
Crush them.
"Crush them." Got it.

01:20.480 --> 01:21.981
Uh, the Canyon People
were hoping

01:22.081 --> 01:23.823
they could have
their women and children back.

01:23.923 --> 01:26.346
Hm. I guess you could do that.
Shut up. Crush them.

01:26.446 --> 01:27.987
"Crush them too." Great.

01:28.087 --> 01:29.629
Oh, uh, this note was left
for you on the door.

01:29.729 --> 01:31.111
Hm.

01:31.211 --> 01:33.873
"Dear neighbour, you are
in violation of Rule 17.4

01:33.973 --> 01:35.955
prohibiting unsanctioned
lawn ornamentation.

01:36.055 --> 01:38.598
Please remove the decapitated
heads immediately.

01:38.698 --> 01:40.240
Signed, the 'Hoa.'"

01:40.340 --> 01:41.721
Who is this Hoa?

01:41.821 --> 01:43.443
I don't know, but it sounds
intimidating.

01:43.543 --> 01:46.686
Like some sort of mythical beast
or barbarian king.

01:46.786 --> 01:50.630
Whoever it is, no one tells
Freya Exaltada what to do.

01:51.631 --> 01:54.234
I will find this Hoa,
and I will destroy it.

01:55.915 --> 01:58.418
That's right, Mommy.
You show 'em who is boss.

01:58.518 --> 02:01.481
Give e'm the ol' one, two!
Sure, sure!

02:03.163 --> 02:05.105
You know what I love
about this job, Devon?

02:05.205 --> 02:07.347
It's that we're doing
actual good in the world.

02:07.447 --> 02:10.430
For instance, without us,
this doll would just be trash.

02:10.530 --> 02:12.752
But now some child
will have a new best friend.

02:12.852 --> 02:16.076
Aah! That...one has a family
of scorpions living in it.

02:16.176 --> 02:17.637
But the point remains.

02:17.737 --> 02:19.799
[ Man moans weakly ]

02:19.899 --> 02:21.561
I'm looking
for the Junkman.

02:21.661 --> 02:23.883
Ah. My package is here.

02:23.983 --> 02:26.646
I was ambushed
by bandits.

02:26.746 --> 02:28.047
It was a slaughter.

02:28.147 --> 02:30.090
Tell my wife...
I love her.

02:30.190 --> 02:32.332
Yeah, sure, pal. Here's
a shiny beak for your troubles.

02:32.432 --> 02:34.434
[ Groans ]

02:35.355 --> 02:36.376
What is it?

02:36.476 --> 02:39.419
[ Mystical music playing ]

02:39.519 --> 02:41.661
They call it
the Gigachron.

02:41.761 --> 02:46.106
Rumour has it its power
transcends time and space.

02:46.206 --> 02:47.747
And more importantly,

02:47.847 --> 02:50.470
some rich schmuck is willing
to pay me a lot of money for it.

02:50.570 --> 02:52.912
Alright.
So, accompanying me

02:53.012 --> 02:55.555
on this
very important sale...

02:55.655 --> 02:58.398
is...

02:58.498 --> 02:59.559
Sid, my golden boy.

02:59.659 --> 03:00.880
Hell yes!

03:00.980 --> 03:02.162
I thought
I was your golden boy.

03:02.262 --> 03:03.763
Nope. It's Sid now.

03:03.863 --> 03:06.886
In fact, Sid, why don't you take
Devon's desk from now on?

03:06.986 --> 03:09.769
Devon, you go sit on that pile
of trash over there.

03:09.869 --> 03:11.871
Alright, let's go, Sid.

03:13.112 --> 03:14.574
Sorry, Devon.

03:14.674 --> 03:16.816
Don't be sorry for Devon.
He's a piece of crap.

03:16.916 --> 03:20.500
♪♪

03:20.600 --> 03:22.222
Hi. Yeah, uh,
the pothole on Main Street

03:22.322 --> 03:24.544
still hasn't been fixed,
and I tried to drive my car

03:24.644 --> 03:26.426
over it the other day, and it
went into a bottomless pit.

03:26.526 --> 03:27.427
[ Loud thud ]
Aah!

03:27.527 --> 03:29.108
♪♪

03:29.208 --> 03:30.190
[ Gasping ]

03:30.290 --> 03:32.992
It is I, Freya Exaltada.

03:33.092 --> 03:35.074
I have come to slay the Hoa.

03:35.174 --> 03:37.357
Ma'am, this is actually
the Homeowners Association.

03:37.457 --> 03:38.518
If you'd like to file
a complaint,

03:38.618 --> 03:40.440
you need to wait your turn.

03:40.540 --> 03:42.522
So you must be
the leader here.

03:42.622 --> 03:44.564
Surprising choice
for an overlord.

03:44.664 --> 03:46.686
Small, mousy,

03:46.786 --> 03:48.848
resting bitch face.

03:48.948 --> 03:51.691
Yes, I am the "overlord,"
I suppose.

03:51.791 --> 03:53.373
[ Chuckles ]

03:53.473 --> 03:55.094
Linda Sherman,
HOA President.

03:55.194 --> 03:58.498
Very well, Linda Sherman,
I challenge you

03:58.598 --> 04:01.060
to hand-to-hand combat
for control of Boomtown.

04:01.160 --> 04:02.502
Oh, no,
we don't do that here.

04:02.602 --> 04:03.503
If you want to be president,

04:03.603 --> 04:05.225
you need to win an election.

04:05.325 --> 04:06.666
An election?

04:06.766 --> 04:09.749
Seems like an insane way
to pick a leader.

04:09.849 --> 04:11.311
Very well.

04:11.411 --> 04:13.473
If those are your terms
of battle, then I accept.

04:13.573 --> 04:16.956
And I promise, when I am
president of the HOA...
Ma'am, your time is up.

04:17.056 --> 04:21.080
...I will crush any
and all stand in my way.

04:21.180 --> 04:22.682
And there will be --
[ Microphone cuts ]

04:22.782 --> 04:25.044
Wow. Really?

04:25.144 --> 04:26.606
[ Scoffs ]
That's crap.

04:26.706 --> 04:29.188
I mean, I don't care,
but that's crap.

04:30.470 --> 04:34.534
[ Dramatic music playing ]

04:34.634 --> 04:36.175
Getting kind of a spooky vibe
from this place.

04:36.275 --> 04:39.018
How -- How much do we know
about this buyer?

04:39.118 --> 04:41.981
I assume he's like
a regular customer of yours?

04:42.081 --> 04:43.583
Nope.
Never met him in my life.

04:43.683 --> 04:45.345
Really?

04:45.445 --> 04:47.547
The Gigachron seems like
an awfully powerful device

04:47.647 --> 04:49.188
to just be handing over
to a complete stranger.

04:49.288 --> 04:51.551
Shouldn't we find out
what his intentions are

04:51.651 --> 04:53.112
or run a background check?

04:53.212 --> 04:55.074
At least get a copy
of his photo I.D., right?

04:55.174 --> 04:58.478
Sid, relax. I've done
these deals millions of times.

04:58.578 --> 05:01.241
I'm sure he's just some guy.

05:01.341 --> 05:04.284
Gentlemen, Ugulus Sleeze
will see you now.

05:04.384 --> 05:06.886
Wait, did she say his name
was Ugulus Sleeze?

05:06.986 --> 05:08.568
[ Mechanical whirring ]

05:08.668 --> 05:13.893
♪♪

05:13.993 --> 05:17.116
[ Chuckles menacingly, growls ]

05:19.759 --> 05:21.381
Welcome.

05:21.481 --> 05:25.625
[ Laughs evilly ]

05:25.725 --> 05:28.007
See? Just some guy.

05:29.969 --> 05:33.353
You have the Gigachron?

05:33.453 --> 05:35.515
Yep. It's right here.

05:35.615 --> 05:37.677
That'll be 30,000
bird beaks.

05:37.777 --> 05:41.681
You said 20,000.

05:41.781 --> 05:43.443
That was last week.
Price went up.

05:43.543 --> 05:48.368
[ Snarls, laughs ]

05:48.468 --> 05:52.812
I like your style.
Get him his money.

05:52.912 --> 05:56.175
♪♪

05:56.275 --> 05:57.417
[ Case rattles ]

05:57.517 --> 05:59.539
I think we're good.

05:59.639 --> 06:01.641
[ Grunts ]

06:02.241 --> 06:04.744
At last, the Gigachron
is within my grasp.

06:04.844 --> 06:07.587
Okay, no, actually, just --
I need to borrow my boss

06:07.687 --> 06:08.908
for a very quick moment.

06:09.008 --> 06:10.830
We need to discuss
a business matter.

06:10.930 --> 06:13.192
Not about you.
What are you doing?

06:13.292 --> 06:15.034
We're in
the middle of a deal.
Okay.

06:15.134 --> 06:18.077
Does anything strike you as
concerning about the situation?

06:18.177 --> 06:19.719
How so?
Oh, I don't know.

06:19.819 --> 06:22.322
Maybe the fact that
Ugulus seems totally evil,

06:22.422 --> 06:24.003
like his greed
and depravity turned him

06:24.103 --> 06:25.445
into something
not quite human.

06:25.545 --> 06:27.567
And also that it lives
in a pool of toxic muck,

06:27.667 --> 06:29.088
which is
maybe his life force.

06:29.188 --> 06:30.770
I feel like any one
of these things

06:30.870 --> 06:32.251
should be a huge red flag.

06:32.351 --> 06:34.253
He seems
like a good guy to me.

06:34.353 --> 06:36.856
Look, he's smiling
and he's being very respectful

06:36.956 --> 06:39.058
about keeping his genitals
below the muck line.

06:39.158 --> 06:41.060
It's just it's really important
to me that my job

06:41.160 --> 06:44.063
doesn't conflict
with my personal values.

06:44.163 --> 06:45.425
It doesn't.

06:45.525 --> 06:46.946
I mean, look, of course,

06:47.046 --> 06:49.749
if we knew Ugulus
was a bad dude,

06:49.849 --> 06:51.991
we wouldn't be
selling him the Gigachron.

06:52.091 --> 06:54.354
But we can't go investigating
every single person

06:54.454 --> 06:56.556
we do business with
for whether they've ever done

06:56.656 --> 06:58.277
anything bad in their lives.

06:58.377 --> 06:59.519
Nor should we.

06:59.619 --> 07:01.561
That's not part of the job.

07:01.661 --> 07:04.484
Okay?
Congrats, Mr. Sleeze.

07:04.584 --> 07:07.767
You are the proud owner
of one new Gigachron.

07:07.867 --> 07:11.891
At last! The power!
The power!

07:11.991 --> 07:13.933
[ Groans ]

07:14.033 --> 07:15.334
Oh, man.
He's licking it.

07:15.434 --> 07:17.256
[ Vocalising ]
Okay, uh, well,

07:17.356 --> 07:19.058
we should probably
hit the road then.

07:19.158 --> 07:20.820
Goodbye forever,
Mr. Sleeze

07:20.920 --> 07:24.023
Wait!
We should celebrate.

07:24.123 --> 07:28.067
Let us from suckle
from the teat of decadence.

07:28.167 --> 07:29.509
Mmm.

07:29.609 --> 07:32.872
Sounds nice, right?
Suckling some teat?

07:32.972 --> 07:35.835
Beep, beep.
The party bus has arrived,

07:35.935 --> 07:40.159
and, uh-oh, the bus driver
has been drinking on the job!

07:40.259 --> 07:41.921
What the hell?

07:42.021 --> 07:45.445
Tai, you made it.
Did the party bus
make a wrong turn?

07:45.545 --> 07:47.166
I thought this was
going to be a rager.

07:47.266 --> 07:49.008
Yeah, it's a raging
local meet-and-greet

07:49.108 --> 07:50.289
to get to know the candidate.

07:50.389 --> 07:51.651
Help yourself
to a lemon square.

07:51.751 --> 07:53.332
We'll get started in a sec.

07:53.432 --> 07:56.416
Oh, man, I can't believe I got
my robo penis polished

07:56.516 --> 07:57.777
for this shit.

07:57.877 --> 07:59.879
[ Sighs ]

08:01.641 --> 08:03.222
Would you like to make
a donation to the campaign?

08:03.322 --> 08:05.425
Every little bit helps.
Oh, yes.

08:05.525 --> 08:06.986
That sounds great.

08:07.086 --> 08:10.149
Ah, shoot.
You know, I forgot my wallet.

08:10.249 --> 08:15.635
Oh, no. And I was going to give
so much money. Darn it.

08:15.735 --> 08:18.518
[ Clears throat ]
Testing, testing.

08:18.618 --> 08:20.440
One, two, three.
Hello, everyone.

08:20.540 --> 08:23.322
So when you elect me
as your next HOA president,

08:23.422 --> 08:26.045
I promise to rule
with an iron fist.

08:26.145 --> 08:28.888
Your houses will burn,
chaos will reign.

08:28.988 --> 08:32.411
And every day will be a barrage
of suffering and misery

08:32.511 --> 08:34.974
until I grant you
the sweet release of death.

08:35.074 --> 08:36.976
Um, yeah.
No, I don't like that.

08:37.076 --> 08:39.138
Okay. Well, it doesn't really
matter what you like,

08:39.238 --> 08:40.740
because I'll be in charge.

08:40.840 --> 08:42.141
Actually, kind of does.

08:42.241 --> 08:43.863
Because these people
won't vote for you

08:43.963 --> 08:46.385
unless you listen to their
whiny little jerkoff problems.

08:46.485 --> 08:48.227
Yeah, exactly.

08:48.327 --> 08:52.351
Oh. Okay. Um...okay.
let's try this again.

08:52.451 --> 08:56.556
I would love to hear
about what you want,

08:56.656 --> 09:00.359
because I care...about you

09:00.459 --> 09:03.803
and don't think that
you're a pathetic worm.

09:03.903 --> 09:05.605
Much better.

09:05.705 --> 09:07.086
Hey, great news.

09:07.186 --> 09:08.768
I just remembered you
can donate online.

09:08.868 --> 09:10.850
Oh, my gosh. That's so great.

09:10.950 --> 09:12.371
Why don't you send me
an e-mail?

09:12.471 --> 09:15.054
Yeah, my e-mail is
fakename at

09:15.154 --> 09:18.417
not-a-real-email-address
dot nothing.

09:18.517 --> 09:22.461
Got it. Is there a dot
between the fake and name?

09:22.561 --> 09:25.705
[ Inhales deeply ]

09:25.805 --> 09:28.187
Ooh, hachi machi!
That's strong stuff!

09:28.287 --> 09:34.113
Blossom is an ancient narcotic
used to access the great divine.

09:34.213 --> 09:37.837
All I know is it's making me
want to bust a freakin' nut.

09:37.937 --> 09:41.200
Hey, what's the matter,
little one?

09:41.300 --> 09:44.443
This is a glorious day.

09:44.543 --> 09:47.567
When I unleash the power
of the Gigachron --

09:47.667 --> 09:49.248
Oh, no, no, no.
Actually, I think the less

09:49.348 --> 09:51.090
I know about your plans
for the Gigachron, the better.

09:51.190 --> 09:53.973
Why don't we talk
about something else?
Hm.

09:54.073 --> 09:55.855
Did you grow up
in this lair,

09:55.955 --> 09:57.577
or did you move here
after college?

09:57.677 --> 10:01.140
The Sleezes ruled
for generations before

10:01.240 --> 10:07.426
before House Benevola overthrew
us, spreading peace in the land.

10:07.526 --> 10:10.710
But that all changes tonight

10:10.810 --> 10:12.471
when I unleash
the power of the --

10:12.571 --> 10:14.153
No, no, no, no, no.
Again. Again.

10:14.253 --> 10:15.875
I do not need to know
what you're doing with it.

10:15.975 --> 10:18.798
How about we will just sit here
and finish our drugs in silence?

10:18.898 --> 10:20.519
Sure, sure. Mm-hmm.

10:20.619 --> 10:22.121
♪♪

10:22.221 --> 10:24.363
I was just gonna say I'm gonna
blow House Benevola away

10:24.463 --> 10:26.445
with the Gigachron.
Damn it, Ugulus! Why?

10:26.545 --> 10:28.608
Oopsies.

10:28.708 --> 10:29.929
[ Inhales deeply ]

10:30.029 --> 10:32.331
Mama, mama, mama!

10:32.431 --> 10:33.693
And...

10:33.793 --> 10:35.775
I busted.
[ Laughs ]

10:35.875 --> 10:38.497
The Battledome used to be a
place where people could gather

10:38.597 --> 10:40.179
and settle disputes.

10:40.279 --> 10:42.301
Now it's covered in trash.

10:42.401 --> 10:45.064
No one's been killed
here in ages.

10:45.164 --> 10:46.986
It's a shame.
[ Spits ]

10:47.086 --> 10:49.508
How dare you suggest your future
queen pick up your trash?

10:49.608 --> 10:51.591
I should bite
your friggin' nuts!

10:51.691 --> 10:54.754
Down, boy! Down! Heel!
Let me at him!
I can tell he's got juicy ones!

10:54.854 --> 10:56.315
[ Shouts indistinctly ]

10:56.415 --> 10:59.518
Hey! Hey!
Down, boy, down.

10:59.618 --> 11:00.840
I'll do it.

11:00.940 --> 11:02.602
No!

11:02.702 --> 11:05.524
No. You're Freya Exaltada.
You answer to no man.

11:05.624 --> 11:08.047
I don't like it either,
but if this is what it takes

11:08.147 --> 11:11.430
to crush Linda and rule the HOA,
I'll it.

11:13.312 --> 11:14.533
Time to take out
the trash.

11:14.633 --> 11:16.736
[ Upbeat synth music playing ]

11:16.836 --> 11:18.257
♪♪

11:18.357 --> 11:20.019
[ Beeping ]

11:20.119 --> 11:29.068
♪♪

11:29.168 --> 11:30.990
Man: Hey, you're there.

11:31.090 --> 11:35.154
We think what you're doing
is pretty cool.

11:35.254 --> 11:36.355
Want some help?

11:36.455 --> 11:45.805
♪♪

11:45.905 --> 11:47.907
Nice work, guys.
We did it.

11:49.068 --> 11:51.010
Hey, beautiful job.

11:51.110 --> 11:53.693
So, do I have your vote?

11:53.793 --> 11:56.615
I should have mentioned you.
I already voted for Linda.

11:56.715 --> 11:59.578
What?! I -- I did exactly
what you asked for.

11:59.678 --> 12:01.981
Yeah, but
I always vote for Linda.

12:02.081 --> 12:03.422
We all do.

12:03.522 --> 12:05.705
In fact, she won the election.
by a landslide.

12:05.805 --> 12:07.827
[ Groans ]

12:07.927 --> 12:10.069
[ Dramatic music playing ]

12:10.169 --> 12:17.276
♪♪

12:17.376 --> 12:22.201
Mommy-y-y-y-y!

12:22.301 --> 12:26.445
Linda-a-a-a-a!

12:26.545 --> 12:29.088
Hey, I'm ready to make
that donation now.

12:29.188 --> 12:31.450
[ Gasps ] Oh, no.
Did I just miss it?

12:31.550 --> 12:33.813
Oh, is it too late?

12:33.913 --> 12:37.276
Oh, no. I'm so sad.

12:38.477 --> 12:40.900
The time has come

12:41.000 --> 12:45.044
to unleash the power
of the Gigachron.

12:46.886 --> 12:48.828
Yes...

12:48.928 --> 12:53.472
Okay, so I have just spoken to
Ugulus, and long story short,

12:53.572 --> 12:55.154
he is definitely evil.

12:55.254 --> 12:56.796
Oh, jeez. He is?

12:56.896 --> 12:59.198
Yeah, he was pretty explicit
that he's planning on using

12:59.298 --> 13:01.320
the Gigachron to blow
a bunch of innocent people.

13:01.420 --> 13:04.203
So obviously we can't
work with him now.

13:04.303 --> 13:06.205
Yeah.

13:06.305 --> 13:08.247
But I also want to make
a lot of money.

13:08.347 --> 13:11.130
So there's that.
But, no, you -- you said

13:11.230 --> 13:13.372
we were okay as long as we
didn't know what his plans are.

13:13.472 --> 13:15.895
Now we do know what they are,
so, what, are we just gonna...

13:15.995 --> 13:17.696
throw away your morals
for a paycheque?

13:17.796 --> 13:18.978
Exactly!

13:19.078 --> 13:21.981
See? You did
learn something today.

13:22.081 --> 13:24.383
The old order falls.

13:24.483 --> 13:27.186
A new order begins.

13:27.286 --> 13:33.152
[ Laughs evilly ]

13:33.252 --> 13:35.755
Aah!

13:35.855 --> 13:37.556
No!

13:37.656 --> 13:40.659
[ Gurgling ]

13:43.983 --> 13:46.125
What did you do?
I stopped Ugulus

13:46.225 --> 13:48.167
before he could kill everyone
with the Gigachron.

13:48.267 --> 13:51.250
The Gigachron
isn't a weapon.

13:51.350 --> 13:53.052
It isn't?
No.

13:53.152 --> 13:55.474
It's a karaoke machine.

13:56.795 --> 13:58.898
[ "Waterfalls" playing ]

13:58.998 --> 14:02.862
Oh, I remember this song.
"Waterfalls" by TLC.

14:02.962 --> 14:04.503
Catchy tune.

14:04.603 --> 14:05.785
Did you know
it was about AIDS?

14:05.885 --> 14:07.306
Guards.

14:07.406 --> 14:10.649
♪ Don't go chasing waterfalls ♪

14:11.210 --> 14:13.712
We find you guilty
of the murder

14:13.812 --> 14:16.876
of our beloved boss
and dear friend, Ugulus Sleeze.

14:16.976 --> 14:18.717
Okay, wait. Timeout
for just a second.

14:18.817 --> 14:20.920
In my defence,
the guy did say he was gonna

14:21.020 --> 14:22.161
blow everyone away.

14:22.261 --> 14:23.762
Yes, he was going to blow them

14:23.862 --> 14:26.605
away with his beautiful
singing voice.

14:26.705 --> 14:28.447
Ugulus was going to bring
the Gigachron to

14:28.547 --> 14:29.688
Lord Benevola's birthday party

14:29.788 --> 14:31.490
and finally end
their silly feud.

14:31.590 --> 14:32.731
Okay, but I mean,
you can see

14:32.831 --> 14:34.333
how I might have
misinterpreted that.

14:34.433 --> 14:36.415
The guy was an insane,
disgusting 30-ton monster,

14:36.515 --> 14:39.218
for God's sake.
Whoa!
So we're fat shaming him now?

14:39.318 --> 14:40.980
No, no, I did--
That's not --

14:41.080 --> 14:43.142
So you just go around killing
every fat person you see.

14:43.242 --> 14:44.864
People like you make me sick.

14:44.964 --> 14:48.107
Can I say that I just hired
this guy, like, a week ago,

14:48.207 --> 14:50.709
and he does not represent
the values of my business.

14:50.809 --> 14:56.075
Okay, clearly...
I owe everyone a huge apology.

14:56.175 --> 15:00.479
I realise now that I have a huge
amount of work to do on myself,

15:00.579 --> 15:06.125
and I appreciate all
of your support on that journey.

15:06.225 --> 15:08.467
I am a work in progress.

15:10.629 --> 15:11.810
[ Whispering ]
Did that work?

15:11.910 --> 15:13.893
Kill them.
[ Weapons powering up ]

15:13.993 --> 15:18.037
Ma'am, we found this holodex
at Mr. Sleeze's tank.

15:21.880 --> 15:23.542
Hello, friends.

15:23.642 --> 15:27.826
If you're seeing this,
then I'm already dead.

15:27.926 --> 15:31.190
Reunited with
my beautiful wife, Janine.

15:31.290 --> 15:33.152
Aw, man. Dead wife.

15:33.252 --> 15:37.877
In these polarised times,
with everyone's squabbling

15:37.977 --> 15:39.718
over who's right
and who's wrong,

15:39.818 --> 15:43.522
we must remember
that we're all human.

15:43.622 --> 15:47.326
We must forgive and rebuild.

15:47.426 --> 15:50.289
Namaste.
Woman: Namaste.

15:50.389 --> 15:51.450
He's right.

15:51.550 --> 15:53.292
You two are free to go.

15:53.392 --> 15:55.054
It's what Ugulus
would have wanted.

15:55.154 --> 15:57.416
Oh.
Yeah. Thank you.

15:57.516 --> 15:59.518
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

16:00.759 --> 16:02.541
I just -- Can I say
for the record as well

16:02.641 --> 16:04.103
my favourite uncle
struggled with weight issues

16:04.203 --> 16:05.104
his whole life.

16:05.204 --> 16:06.625
Get out of here!
Okay.

16:06.725 --> 16:08.908
Sid, you've done enough harm
for one day.

16:09.008 --> 16:11.010
Let's go.
Okay.

16:13.852 --> 16:15.634
Linda Sherman!

16:15.734 --> 16:17.036
Again with the door.

16:17.136 --> 16:21.720
You had the gall
to challenge me in battle.

16:21.820 --> 16:24.323
I declare...

16:24.423 --> 16:25.925
defeat.
[ Gasps ]

16:26.025 --> 16:27.806
I was a fool to believe
I could challenge a ruler

16:27.906 --> 16:29.969
as omnipotent as you.

16:30.069 --> 16:31.971
Shame, 'cause I actually kind
of like helping the community.

16:32.071 --> 16:35.014
But that's
all in the past now,

16:35.114 --> 16:37.937
and you must
chop my head off.

16:38.037 --> 16:39.218
Oh.

16:39.318 --> 16:41.020
No, we don't kill you
if you lose.

16:41.120 --> 16:44.423
Huh?
No, in fact, the person
who wins second place

16:44.523 --> 16:46.705
automatically becomes
vice president.

16:46.805 --> 16:48.707
I mean, that is if you want it.

16:48.807 --> 16:52.591
Oh. Uh, well,
I hadn't considered that.

16:52.691 --> 16:56.915
I mean...I suppose
I could be...vice president.

16:57.015 --> 16:59.878
If that's how it works?
Yep. Hmm.

16:59.978 --> 17:02.441
Thank you, Linda.
You are a merciful god.

17:02.541 --> 17:07.086
My children's children will
sing songs of your greatness.

17:07.186 --> 17:08.767
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

17:08.867 --> 17:11.130
Freya: We're planning so much
cool stuff for the neighbourhood.

17:11.230 --> 17:12.611
Every Sunday,
we're turning the Battledome

17:12.711 --> 17:13.973
into a farmer's market.

17:14.073 --> 17:15.174
Oh, and at
the end of the month

17:15.274 --> 17:17.376
we're hosting
a huge blood orgy.

17:17.476 --> 17:18.497
My idea.

17:18.597 --> 17:20.980
How is this possible?

17:21.080 --> 17:22.741
My infallible leader
destroyed,

17:22.841 --> 17:25.424
my entire sense
of reality shattered.

17:25.524 --> 17:28.147
Do I even exist?

17:28.247 --> 17:30.789
Are we all but shadows dancing
upon a cave wall?

17:30.889 --> 17:32.431
Aww, cheer up, boy.

17:32.531 --> 17:33.872
Hey. Hey.

17:33.972 --> 17:36.996
Truth is...

17:37.096 --> 17:40.719
this is all a part of my secret
plan to take over the town.

17:40.819 --> 17:43.122
It is?
[ Chuckles ]

17:43.222 --> 17:45.204
First, I have befriend
the neighbours,

17:45.304 --> 17:48.047
helping them with their issues,
offering a shoulder to lean on.

17:48.147 --> 17:51.610
Then, after many years of
earning their trust and respect,

17:51.710 --> 17:56.015
right when they least expect it,
the HOA will be mine!

17:56.115 --> 17:59.218
[ Both laughing evilly ]

17:59.318 --> 18:01.060
Oh, hey, Frey-Frey.

18:01.160 --> 18:02.621
The girls are coming over later
for wine o'clock

18:02.721 --> 18:03.822
if you want to join.

18:03.922 --> 18:05.744
Yes, bitch.
You know it, girl.

18:05.844 --> 18:08.207
[ Laughs ] Okay, bitch!

18:10.129 --> 18:11.670
Um...

18:11.770 --> 18:14.193
wine o'clock
is also part of the plan.

18:14.293 --> 18:15.954
[ Snickers ]

18:16.054 --> 18:18.056
Truly wicked.
I know.

18:23.902 --> 18:26.685
Thanks for the ride home,
and I'm really sorry again

18:26.785 --> 18:29.848
about ruining your big deal
and killing that guy.

18:29.948 --> 18:31.650
Yeah, it's fine.

18:31.750 --> 18:34.133
I wouldn't be much of a mentor
if I gave up on you

18:34.233 --> 18:36.095
after your first mistake.

18:36.195 --> 18:38.177
You're still my golden boy.

18:38.277 --> 18:40.739
Thank you.

18:40.839 --> 18:44.823
Besides, at least today wasn't
a total bust. Check this out.

18:44.923 --> 18:46.785
I stole it
from Ugulus's nightstand

18:46.885 --> 18:49.068
while the guards
were fishing out his dead body.

18:49.168 --> 18:51.390
That's -- That's really bad.

18:51.490 --> 18:52.991
Well, who's to say?

18:53.091 --> 18:55.033
What if I told you
I was going to sell the watch

18:55.133 --> 18:56.195
to buy more drugs?

18:56.295 --> 18:57.676
That makes it much worse.

18:57.776 --> 18:59.037
Eh, who's to say?

18:59.137 --> 19:00.479
Well, if you'll excuse me,

19:00.579 --> 19:03.942
I have some important...
business to attend to.

19:08.867 --> 19:10.609
Hi. I missed you.
Hey.

19:10.709 --> 19:12.531
Did you have a good day
at work?

19:12.631 --> 19:14.333
I don't know that
the words good and bad

19:14.433 --> 19:17.616
have any meaning
for me anymore.

19:17.716 --> 19:19.778
I did make money,
though.

19:19.878 --> 19:21.900
♪♪

19:22.000 --> 19:24.503
How was your day, Freya?
It was good. Thanks for asking.

19:24.603 --> 19:26.625
♪♪

19:26.725 --> 19:28.947
♪♪

19:29.047 --> 19:33.112
♪ Don't go chasing waterfalls ♪

19:33.212 --> 19:38.717
♪ Please stick to the rivers and
the lakes that you're used to ♪

19:38.817 --> 19:44.563
♪ I know that you're gonna have
it your way or nothing at all ♪

19:44.663 --> 19:49.328
♪ But I think
you're moving too fast ♪

19:49.428 --> 19:51.570
♪♪

19:51.670 --> 19:54.653
♪ I seen a rainbow yesterday,
but too many storms ♪

19:54.753 --> 19:58.096
♪ Have come and gone, leaving a
trace of not one God-given ray ♪

19:58.196 --> 20:00.018
♪ Is it because my life is
10 shades of grey, I pray ♪

20:00.118 --> 20:03.262
♪ All 10 fade away, seldom
praise Him for the sunny days ♪

20:03.362 --> 20:05.784
♪ And like His promise is true,
only my faith can undo ♪

20:05.884 --> 20:08.427
♪ The many chances I blew
to bring my life to anew ♪

20:08.527 --> 20:11.150
♪ Clear blue
and unconditional skies ♪

20:11.250 --> 20:14.393
♪ Have dried the tears from
my eyes, no more lonely cries ♪

20:14.493 --> 20:17.676
♪ Don't go chasing waterfalls ♪

20:17.776 --> 20:20.859
♪ Please stick
to the rivers... ♪
